# v1.87.0 â€” Guest stats refactor

Tracking: refactor "Guest" from a per-team pseudo-player on the roster to an
event-level concept on `MatchEvent`. Stale-worktree protocol ran clean
(parent fast-forward + worktree rebase onto `origin/main` v1.86.0).

## M1 â€” Own-goal model surfaced + plan refined

### Existing own-goal model

**Schema** ([prisma/schema.prisma:801-849](prisma/schema.prisma)):
- `MatchEvent.goalType: GoalType?` (line 808). Enum values
  `OPEN_PLAY | SET_PIECE | PENALTY | OWN_GOAL`.
- `MatchEvent.beneficiaryTeamId: String?` (line 820, FK to `LeagueTeam`,
  ON DELETE SET NULL, indexed) â€” added in v1.82.0 to record which team the
  goal counts toward, decoupling team attribution from scorer team.
- `MatchEvent.scorerId: String` â€” currently **NOT NULL**. Will need to
  become nullable for guest goals.
- `MatchEvent.assisterId: String?` â€” already nullable.
- Legacy `Goal.isOwnGoal Boolean` column (line 865) is the pre-v1.42.0
  model and is no longer the canonical store. New work uses
  `MatchEvent.goalType`.

**Score recompute** ([src/lib/matchScore.ts:99-133](src/lib/matchScore.ts)):
For a non-OG event, the goal counts toward the scorer's team (or the
explicit `beneficiaryTeamId` post-v1.82.0). For `goalType: 'OWN_GOAL'`,
the scorer is a player on the team that conceded; the goal flips to the
OPPOSITE team. When `beneficiaryTeamId` is set, the recompute trusts it
directly; when null (legacy rows), it falls back to the scorer-team
derivation (and flip-on-OG).

**Stats leaderboard**
([src/components/admin/StatsTab.tsx:106-139](src/components/admin/StatsTab.tsx)):
`buildScorerStatsFromEvents()` filters out OG events from individual goal
totals (`if (!isOG) ...`). The match-level scoreline is handled by
`recomputeMatchScore`; this is the per-player leaderboard only. **OG
assists are not credited either** (the assist increment is inside the
`if (!isOG)` branch).

**UI surfaces** â€” admin event editor and player goal-submit form both
have a goal-type dropdown with "Own goal" as the fourth option, and a
contextual hint "OG: pick from the OPPOSING team":
- Admin: [src/components/admin/StatsTab.tsx:741-790](src/components/admin/StatsTab.tsx)
- Player: [src/components/matchday/SubmitGoalForm.tsx:404-417](src/components/matchday/SubmitGoalForm.tsx)

Both UIs flip the scorer dropdown's primary-team grouping when goal type
is OWN_GOAL: `scorerPrimaryTeamId = goalType === 'OWN_GOAL' ?
opposingTeamId : beneficiaryTeamId` ([SubmitGoalForm.tsx:176](src/components/matchday/SubmitGoalForm.tsx),
[StatsTab.tsx:621](src/components/admin/StatsTab.tsx)).

